thread.title: UNT interim coach vows to bring back fun
thread.title_full: UNT interim coach vows to bring back fun | Dallas Morning News

author: Brett Vito
title: UNT interim coach vows to bring back fun
text:
DENTON -- Mike Canales vowed to bring back fun to the football program in his second stint as interim head coach.
Canales took over for Dan McCarney, who was fired five games into his fifth season following a 66-7 loss to Portland State on Saturday.
"We are going to try to bring some excitement and fun back," Canales said.
Canales, who has banned his players from posting on social media, also served as UNT's interim head coach in the 2010 season.
